<subsection xml:id="subsec-determining-trigonometric-ratios-using-calculator">
    <title>Determining Trigonometric Ratios Using a Calculator</title>
    <p>
        Trigonometric ratios sine (<m>sin</m>), cosine (<m>cos</m>), and tangent(<m>tan</m>) are used to 
        relate the angles and sides of a right-angled triangle. When given an acute angle, 
        a calculator can be used to determine these ratios accurately.
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{How to determine trigonometric ratios using a calculator}</m>.
    </p>
    <image source="/Calculator.jpg" width="50%">
        <shortdescription>calculator</shortdescription>
    </image>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Ensure the calculator is in degree mode.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Press the "<c>MODE</c>" button and select "<c>DEG</c>" (if using a scientific calculator).
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Enter the angle value.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                For example, to find <m>sin\,30^\circ</m>, type:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Press <c>sin</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>30</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            The calculator should display <m>0.5</m> or some calculator will display <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Repeat for cosine and tangent.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>cos\,30^\circ</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Press <c>cos</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>30</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                The calculator should display <m>0.8660...</m> or some calculator will display <m>\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>tan\,30^\circ</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Press <c>tan</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>30</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                The calculator should display <m>0.57735...</m> or some calculator will display <m>\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    <p>
        <term>These values correspond to the exact values
        found using the unit circle or a right-angled triangle.</term>
    </p>
    <p>
        <term>For any acute angle the calculator can be used to find the corresponding values of the trigonometry.</term>
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Work in pairs}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <term>What you require:</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Scientific calculators or any other calculator having <m>sin</m>,<m>cos</m> and <m>tan</m> battons.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Protractor and ruler (for optional verification with a drawn triangle).
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Worksheet with a table.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Turn on your scientific calculator.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Ensure your calculator is set to degree mode (not radians).
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        For each given angle (0°, 25°, 30°, etc.), do the following;
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Press the sin button followed by the angle, then note the value.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Press the cos button followed by the angle, then note the value.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Press the tan button followed by the angle, then note the value.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Record all values in the table below.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Use a calculator to find the sine, cosine, and tangent 
                                    of the given angles, and fill in the table.
                                </p>
                                <tabular halign="center" bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                                    <row header="yes">
                                        <cell>Angle (<m>^\circ</m>)</cell>
                                        <cell><m>{\color{blue} sin}</m></cell>
                                        <cell><m>{\color{blue} cos}</m></cell>
                                        <cell><m>{\color{blue} tan}</m></cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>0^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>25^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>30^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>45^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>60^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>75^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell><m>90^\circ</m></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        <cell></cell>
                                        
                                    </row>
                                </tabular>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Observe and Answer
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Observe the values of sin in your table. Do they increase or decrease?
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Compare the cosine values for different angles.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Why does <m>tan\,90^\circ</m> display a syntax error?
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Use calculator to find the following;(write your answer to <m>\textbf{4 decimal places}</m>).
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>sin\,40^\circ \quad cos\, 40^\circ \quad tan\,40^\circ</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                Ensure the calculator is in degree mode
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,40^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>sin</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>40</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,40^\circ=0.6428</m>
                        </p>

                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,40^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>cos</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>40</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,40^\circ=0.7660</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,40^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>tan</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>40</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,40^\circ=0.8391</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Find <m>sin\,25^\circ \quad cos\, 25^\circ \quad tan\,25^\circ</m> using calculator .
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,25^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>sin</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>25</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,25^\circ=0.4226</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,25^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>cos</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>25</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,25^\circ=0.9063</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,25^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>tan</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>25</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,25^\circ=0.4663</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                What is the value of <m>sin\,65^\circ \quad cos\, 65^\circ \quad tan\,65^\circ</m> in your calculator?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,65^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>sin</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>65</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>sin\,65^\circ=0.9063</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,65^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>cos</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>65</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>cos\,65^\circ=0.4226</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,65^\circ</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press <c>tan</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>65</c> <m>\to</m> Press <c>=</c>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>tan\,65^\circ=2.1445</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Exercises}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Use a calculator to determine the following trigonometric ratios:
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Find <m>sin\,35^\circ \quad cos\, 35^\circ \quad tan\,35^\circ</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Find <m>sin\,50^\circ \quad cos\, 50^\circ \quad tan\,50^\circ</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Find <m>sin\,15^\circ \quad cos\, 15^\circ \quad tan\,15^\circ</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Find <m>sin\,75^\circ \quad cos\, 75^\circ \quad tan\,75^\circ</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    
     
   
   


   

    
    




    
